dcterms:description: The Kaggle DR dataset consists of color fundus images graded by severity of diabetic retinopathy (DR) according to the International Clinical Diabetic Retinopathy severity scale. It is used for training, validation, and testing of deep learning models for DR detection.
dcterms:title: Kaggle DR dataset

dcterms:creator: Age-Related Eye Disease Study Research Group
dcterms:description: The Age-Related Eye Disease Study (AREDS) dataset includes digitalized color fundus images from a long-term prospective study of age-related macular degeneration (AMD) and cataract. It contains images graded by severity of AMD.
dcterms:title: Age-Related Eye Disease Study (AREDS) dataset

dcterms:description: DiaretDB1 is a diabetic retinopathy database consisting of color fundus images with manually delineated lesions by medical experts. It includes annotations for various types of DR lesions.
dcterms:title: DiaretDB1

dcterms:description: EUGENDA is a multi-center database for clinical and molecular analysis of age-related macular degeneration (AMD). It includes color fundus images with annotations for AMD-related lesions.
dcterms:title: EUGENDA
